The `generateNotStrictlyPositiveExceptionAssertion` method is used to generate the assertion statement for `NotStrictlyPositiveException`. It iterates over the parameters and checks if each parameter is an integer. If it is, it adds a condition description to the list. The assertion statement is then generated by joining the condition descriptions with " || ".
